<div class="gut-col" style="padding:54px 12px 0 0">#</div>
<div style="padding:48px 0 26px 30px">
  <div style="font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:12px; color:var(--accent); margin-bottom:16px; letter-spacing:.02em">writ / render.md</div>
  <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-display); font-weight:800; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 72; font-size:clamp(34px,5vw,56px); letter-spacing:-.04em; line-height:1.02; color:var(--foreground); max-width:15ch">Render what your agent writes<span style="color:var(--accent)">.</span></h1>
  <p style="max-width:50ch; margin-top:18px; font-size:clamp(15.5px,1.6vw,18px); line-height:1.55; color:var(--muted)">Your agent streams Markdown. Writ opens and renders it — Mermaid, KaTeX, HTML. Every scratch you keep stays searchable.</p>
  <div style="display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:11px; margin-top:26px">
    <a href="#download" class="v2-btn-primary" style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:9px; height:48px; padding:0 24px; border-radius:11px; background:var(--accent); color:var(--accent-foreground); font-weight:600; font-size:15.5px; box-shadow:0 8px 24px -8px var(--glow)">Download Writ</a>
    <button type="button" data-cmd="demoRender" class="v2-btn-ghost" style="display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:8px; height:48px; padding:0 20px; border-radius:11px; cursor:pointer; background:transparent; color:var(--foreground); border:1px solid var(--border); font-weight:550; font-size:15.5px">
      <span style="font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:12px; color:var(--accent)">▸</span> Run it below
    </button>
  </div>
</div>
